originalText.text: Fabiola and Joe are wonderful people and they will take great care of your child. As a mother of a child who was lucky enough to attend this warm, supportive, and educational daycare, I am sure your child will be happy here. They have years of experience and support the child and their whole family in any way they can!

originalText.text: Fabiola watched me when I was a toddler (that would be around 1990!) and even though I was quite young, I still recall how loved and nurtured I felt in her care. I now have a son of my own and she has watched him too! I knew that under her watch, he was going to have fun and it helped put my mind at ease.

originalText.text:
Fabiola and Joe just attended the high school graduation party of our daughter and oldest child.  So, they’ve known her since she was six months old and we’ve been so fortunate and blessed that they have been an integral part of her life—and our lives—for the last 17-1/2 years.  Fabiola cared for our son as well (he starts 9th grade in the fall).

While we of course didn’t see Fabiola & Joe as often after our kids started school, they always came to our children’s birthday parties as they got older and, now, running into Fabiola or Joe on the street is a real treat.  They always want to know about our children, what they’re up to, and about my husband and me.

I wrote that they’re a part of our lives, but, really, they’re more than that; they’re a part of our family.

Annie Niermann, Andy Beck, Izzie and Aaron
